    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Items taken as spoils, remembrances, or proof of victory in battle. Examples are scalps taken from the fallen enemy and the piles of arms and armor collected and displayed after Greek and Roman military victories. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
